<subSubSection id="62C30CE3FC11FF87F181AE5B3581FB1F" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" type="discussion">
<paragraph id="2A665F68FC11FF87F181AE5B357FFCED" blockId="109.[189,303,779,805]" box="[189,303,779,805]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
<heading id="712EE804FC11FF87F181AE5B357FFCED" bold="true" box="[189,303,779,805]" fontSize="11" level="3" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" reason="3">
<emphasis id="18AD837AFC11FF87F181AE5B357FFCED" bold="true" box="[189,303,779,805]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Remarks</emphasis>
</heading>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="2A665F68FC11FF87F181AE693581FB1F" blockId="109.[189,1399,825,1239]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">
This species has widely been regarded as the spring or early summer brood of 
<taxonomicName id="EDD924EBFC11FF87F5B3AE693127FC9B" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[1167,1399,825,851]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuratus">
<emphasis id="18AD837AFC11FF87F5B3AE693127FC9B" box="[1167,1399,825,851]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Ophion obscuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
but has been shown to be univoltine, at least in Norhern Europe (Mark Shaw, NMS, pers. com.). Apart from the phenological differentiation it is also smaller on average with a lower number of flagellomeres and a small but consistent difference in the shape of the occipital carina at the junction with the hypostomal carina. The taxonomic history of this species is rather complex and accounted for in the Discussion: “The 
<taxonomicName id="EDD924EBFC11FF87F0E2AEB93693FBCB" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[478,707,1001,1027]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuratus">
<emphasis id="18AD837AFC11FF87F0E2AEB93693FBCB" box="[478,707,1001,1027]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Ophion obscuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
aggregate”. To stabilize the name a 
<typeStatus id="F562E1CAFC11FF87F549AEBA3084FBCC" box="[1141,1236,1002,1028]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">neotype</typeStatus>
is designated (
<figureCitation id="B2E243EDFC11FF87F1FAA95C3570FBEF" box="[198,288,1036,1063]" captionStart="Fig" captionStartId="123.[189,232,1947,1973]" captionTargetBox="[189,1398,680,1905]" captionTargetId="figure@123.[189,1399,679,1905]" captionTargetPageId="123" captionText="Fig. 50. Ophion variegatus Rudow, 1883, neotype, ♀ (MNHN). A. Habitus, lateral view. B. Epicnemial carina, lateroventral view. C. Occipital carina, lateroventral view. D. Labels." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.3476516" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/3476516/files/figure.png" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Fig. 50</figureCitation>
A–D). The molecular analysis for the presumed aggregate around this species is weak and its potential genetic delimitation towards 
<taxonomicName id="EDD924EBFC11FF87F3EFA96037D2FB82" authorityName="Fabricius" authorityYear="1798" box="[723,898,1072,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="obscuratus">
<emphasis id="18AD837AFC11FF87F3EFA96037D2FB82" box="[723,898,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">O. obscuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and 
<taxonomicName id="EDD924EBFC11FF87F2F6A9603155FB82" authority="Johansson" authorityName="Johansson &amp; Cederberg" authorityYear="2019" box="[970,1285,1072,1098]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="autumnalis" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="18AD837AFC11FF87F2F6A960302BFB82" box="[970,1147,1072,1098]" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">O. autumnalis</emphasis>
Johansson
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="039E3E01FC11FF87F42FA9603127FB82" box="[1299,1399,1072,1098]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
therefore remain uncertain. Furthermore an additional potential species in the aggregate is indicated by the molecular analysis (STI-NJBC: 199, 316). A wider revision of the Western Palaearctic 
<taxonomicName id="EDD924EBFC11FF87F421A9263511FB7B" authority="Johansson &amp; Cederberg, 2019" authorityName="Johansson &amp; Cederberg" authorityYear="2019" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Ophion" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" sensu="lato" species="obscuratus" status="s. lat.">
<emphasis id="18AD837AFC11FF87F421A9263511FB7B" italics="true" pageId="109" pageNumber="110">Ophion obscuratus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<taxonomicNameLabel id="039E3E01FC11FF87F07BA9CA35D9FB7B" box="[327,393,1177,1204]" pageId="109" pageNumber="110" sensu="lato">s. lat.</taxonomicNameLabel>
, including molecular methods, is probably necessary to clearify the taxonomy of this problematic aggregate.
</paragraph>
</subSubSection>
